cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image synthesis using multi-modal MRI data. The use of neural networks for learning representations and generating missing modalities suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed layer-wise multi-modal fusion strategy and the use of a Mixed Fusion Block (MFB) indicate that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the focus on medical imaging and the use of MRI data suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
